# Shared AI Guidance

Canonical AI guidance lives in `.ai/`. Prefer adding durable agent instructions there, with `.cursor/` and `.claude/` containing lightweight references.

When adding or changing database models, Prisma schema, model repositories, or CRUD data access, read `.ai/skills/add-data-model-to-database/SKILL.md` before making changes.

When adding new pages, routes, or feature page content to any Next.js app, read `.ai/skills/add-new-page/SKILL.md` before making changes.

When adding a new app to the monorepo, creating a new directory or package.json under `apps/`, or setting up any new runnable service (Next.js app, API server, webhook listener, worker, preview server, etc.), read `.ai/skills/add-new-app/SKILL.md` before making changes.

When adding or using icons in app code (apps/*), read `.ai/skills/add-icon/SKILL.md` before making changes. Never import directly from lucide-react in app code.

When creating a new project-level AI skill (SKILL.md), read `.ai/skills/create-skill/SKILL.md` before making changes.

When adding a modal, dialog, confirm dialog, alert dialog, drawer, or any overlay triggered by a user action, read `.ai/skills/add-modal-or-confirm-dialog/SKILL.md` before making changes.

Always use ESM `import`/`export` syntax. Never use `require()` or `module.exports`. This applies to all source code, config files, scripts, and generated code across the entire monorepo.
